ACADEMIC USE NOTICE:

This software was originally developed as part of a Master's thesis in Embedded 
Systems & IoT Engineering. While the code is provided under the MIT License for 
open source use, we kindly request that academic users cite the original work 
when using this software in research or academic contexts.

Suggested Citation:
Amoah, F. (2022). Design and Implementation of a Solar-Assisted WSN-LoRa IoT 
Framework for Real-Time Forest Fire Detection and Monitoring. Master's Thesis, 
Ecole SUP Management. Available: https://github.com/amoahfrank/forest-fire-wsn-thesis

COMMERCIAL USE:

This software may be used commercially under the terms of the MIT License. 
However, users are encouraged to contribute improvements back to the open 
source community and to consider the environmental impact and safety 
critical nature of forest fire detection systems.

DISCLAIMER:

This software is designed for forest fire detection and monitoring purposes. 
While it has been developed with safety and reliability in mind, users must 
conduct their own validation and testing before deploying in safety-critical 
environments. The authors assume no liability for the use of this software 
in real-world fire detection scenarios.

For questions about licensing, commercial use, or academic collaboration, 
please contact: f.amoah@frankholds.win
